# Cursor Browser Agent Rule

**Purpose**: Guide for using Cursor Browser tools to interact with websites, test applications, and preview local development servers.

---

## üß≠ What Cursor Browser Does

Cursor Browser lets the AI Agent **see and interact with websites directly** inside your editor:
- Open and navigate web pages
- Click, scroll, and type
- Capture screenshots
- Read console logs and network traffic
- Run accessibility checks
- Test responsive designs

**No extra setup needed** - works out of the box.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Opening the Browser

### Inline Pane (Recommended for Preview)
Runs inside Cursor - best for quick previews of local dev servers.

```
@browser open http://localhost:4200
```

### External Chrome Window (Recommended for Testing)
Full Chrome session - great for comprehensive web testing.

```
@browser open --chrome http://localhost:4200
```

